column2: I‚Äôm in the @AntonymNFT whitelist chat and it‚Äôs embarrassing. People selling for 5-10x mint and they‚Äôre getting called out as paper hands. Oddly enough, 1+ eth is more than most people make in a month. It‚Äôs a toxic culture. Taking profits IS NOT paper handing. It‚Äôs smart.

8. i do all of this stuff, WITH A TEAM, and still sometimes we get bamboozled. that's showbiz, baby. you don't get outsized returns with no risk. it's impossible. just make sure you aren't risking ETH that you need. because nothing is guaranteed profit.

7. i'm lucky enough to have an entire community at @weareilliquid to do most of the DD for me. consider joining a reputable group and working with the community. doesn't have to be us. it can be anyone. although @EtherOrcs and @CyberKongz are top class as well.

6. on mint day watch how fast the project actually mints. if you have WL, congrats, you have a free call option with no risk. you can simply wait and see. i don't mint until i've seen significant volume. usually >30-40%.
5. how active is the discord compared to the number of members? 80k members but only 10 messages in 10 minutes? all bots. ~1/3 of all members should be "online" at any given time.

4. what communities are backing this project? whitelist spots usually go to known, respected communities that tend to hold (shout out @weareilliquid). there should be some overlap (kongz, orcs, mice, etc). no? be careful.
3. is a rapper or athlete involved? do they know about blockchain tech? no? exit immediately.

2. look at the roadmap. does it make any sense at all? do you think the people running the project are actually capable of executing. be realistic. if they're a bunch of chads do you really think they know how to make a game in unreal? i'm a chad so it's ok for me to say it.
